# Part 3 – Function with Parameters

Instead of always printing the same thing:

```python
def greet():
    print("Hello")
```

We can make it flexible.

```python
def greet(name):
    print("Hello", name)

greet("Srujan")
greet("Alice")
greet("Bob")
```

Output

```
Hello Srujan
Hello Alice
Hello Bob
```

The value inside the brackets is called a **parameter**.

